description:
My place is close to the east river, near Williamsburg and Manhattan bridges, amazing local restaurants including Bacaro, Forgtmenot, Barrio Chino, Dimes, The Fat Radish, Scarr's Pizza and so many more! You’ll love my place because it's located right on the boarder of Lower East Side and Chinatown, the coolest hood in Manhattan! My studio has amazing light, park view, Cali vibes in NYC. The bed is super cozy. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers. XO

I LOVE my studio. It's as open and spacious for its size. Modern warmth with light and love. Minimalism, light & airy.

hosts.about:
California transplant .. i say COOL .. A LOT! and RAD! and wear all black .. 
fashion designer
quiet in my apartment .. respect the neighbors .. walls are paper thin!
extremely clean and expect the same
respectful of other peoples property and privacy
love to travel .. meet new people .. experience different places, things, cultures
food is awesome
nature is rad .. thanks nature

As a host ..
expect a clean warm open space with little details ..
golden rule .. do unto others as you wish done unto you .. 
i love my space and things .. please love them and leave them as you found them :))
most personal effects have been removed so you can feel and get as comfortable on your trip as if you lived here! I love unpacking my suitcase even if it's only for a couple days. Makes me feel more immersed with a locals only kinda vibe :))

get out and explore! I know I am!

XO
